missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as a calibrated obstruction hunt and weak as a live proof route. Its best instinct is correct: if Step 011 killed the generic coupled energy-helicity story, then any remaining helical route has to survive exact packet completion, mixed-helicity restoration, and physical-space reinsertion. That is the right bar.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The problem is that the chain still overestimates what "exact packet structure" is likely to buy. Exact helical triad bookkeeping is real, but real is not the same as coercive. Waleffe-style interaction geometry, same-helicity suppression, and decimated-sector advantages have been around for a long time. The hard issue is not whether one can write a packet-complete ledger. The hard issue is whether any sign or exclusion effect survives full mixed-helicity completion, shell summation, localization, pressure restoration, and insertion into an LEI/CKN-facing endpoint. That is exactly where these ideas usually die.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- Conjugate completion, spectator leakage, and mixed-helicity bookkeeping are precisely the features that tend to erase the pretty sign picture seen in restricted sectors. The chain talks as if including them is a completeness upgrade. In practice they may be the reason no gain survives.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:44:- Thin-sector risk is enormous here. The promoted mechanism may live on one coherent packet family, one triad geometry, or one polarized subpopulation. That is not enough unless the chain proves that the bad transfer cannot simply reroute through the uncontrolled families.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- Prior-art comparison should happen before any mechanism is promoted, not after. This chain lives right next to Waleffe-type triad analysis, helical shell heuristics, same-helicity suppression folklore, and decimated-model literature. Waiting until Step 5 to compare against them invites rediscovery theater.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:68:- A failed lemma may actually be the most valuable positive outcome of this whole route. The chain should say that more aggressively. The likely honest artifact is an obstruction showing exactly where mixed-helicity completion or localization destroys the sign gain.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:70:- The overlap verdict also needs to address redundancy at the level of mechanism, not only vocabulary. If the route rediscovers that same-helicity interactions look better than mixed ones, that is not a new route even if the packet language is more exact.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:79:- The failure taxonomy is too tidy. In reality this route is likely to fail for several reasons at once: prior-art overlap, mixed-helicity collapse, reconstruction loss, and endpoint mismatch. Forcing a single label can understate how overdetermined the failure is.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:93:The route sits in the immediate neighborhood of known helical triad geometry, same-helicity advantages, decimated models, and shell-transfer folklore. That does not kill the chain, but it means the default expectation should be redundancy unless the route identifies a genuinely new full-system effect very early.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:113:- The chain correctly refuses to count same-helicity or decimated-sector gains as evidence by themselves.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:114:- It explicitly demands mixed-helicity restoration, spectator leakage accounting, and physical-space reconstruction. Those are the right debts.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md:122:The honest question is not whether exact helical packet structure exists. It does. The honest question is whether any packet-complete effect survives full mixed-helicity completion and then still has enough one-sided strength left after summation, localization, and endpoint insertion to matter for beyond-De Giorgi. That is a much harsher test, and this chain gives too many opportunities to confuse symbolic exactness with real leverage before that test is passed.
