missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain had the correct instinct that any surviving helical route must clear exact packet completion, mixed-helicity restoration, and physical-space reinsertion. But it still gave too much room for target shopping, overread exact symbolic structure as possible coercive leverage, and placed the hardest bottlenecks too late. The right repair is not to kill the branch outright. It is to turn it into an obstruction-first helical-symbol program with an earlier endpoint-exchange gate, an earlier prior-art screen, and a stricter rule that no packet mechanism is promoted before it has an explicit inequality and a quantified share of the actual theorem-facing burden.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-03.md:37:Waleffe-type triad geometry, same-helicity preference, and decimated-sector advantages sit too close to this route to be checked only near the end. Prior-art comparison should happen before any mechanism is promoted. The attacker is also right that a failed lemma or exact obstruction is a first-class success mode here, not a consolation prize.
