missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This chain is attacking the right high-upside question, but it is structurally at risk of confusing an algebraic rewrite with a usable estimate. The central analogy to SQG is weaker than the chain admits: in SQG, the first-order commutator is tied to scalar transport and a linear constitutive law, while in NS the Lamb-vector / vorticity / Helmholtz forms are mostly equivalent repackagings of the same quadratic vector interaction. Unless the chain screens candidates at the level of the actual localized or truncated estimate that matters, it can spend several steps rediscovering textbook identities and then either overclaim a negative result or drift into Chain 03's Beltrami geometry.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:14:- The step risks re-deriving facts the mission already treats as established: scalar truncation survives in SQG, vector truncation does not in NS; the vorticity route still lands at the same `beta = 4/3` barrier; Beltrami cancellation is exact but fragile. If the comparison matrix just restates those points, Step 1 produces paperwork, not progress.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:36:- Testing exact Beltrami flows is a weak stress test for an allegedly generic NS mechanism. Exact Beltrami is a highly nongeneric symmetry class where the Lamb vector vanishes by design. Success there proves almost nothing.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:37:- The mission context already records the crucial negative fact: the Beltrami-based cancellation does not survive even very small perturbations from alignment. That means Step 3 is in danger of rediscovering an established fragility rather than testing a genuinely open point.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:38:- "Small perturbations away from Beltrami alignment" is underspecified. Small in `L^2`, `H^1`, direction field, or a pointwise angle deficit? These are mathematically very different. Without fixing the perturbation metric, the stress test is not interpretable.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:40:- This step overlaps heavily with Chain 03. Once the test object becomes "Beltrami alignment plus perturbations," the chain has drifted from algebraic reformulation into geometry-first fragility analysis. That weakens the claim that Chain 02 is meaningfully distinct.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:42:Concrete failure mode: Step 3 may produce an inequality that looks favorable in an exact or nearly exact Beltrami regime, then collapse outside that regime. At that point the chain has not found an SQG-type mechanism; it has merely recovered the known statement that special alignment depletes the nonlinearity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:51:- The step also inherits the contamination from Step 3. If the surviving mechanism is really a near-Beltrami geometry effect, then the chain should close by handing that result to the geometry branch, not by presenting it as an algebraic reformulation win.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:53:Concrete failure mode: Step 4 can produce a memo that sounds definitive while the underlying work only ruled out a handful of obvious rewrites and one nongeneric Beltrami-based pilot.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:68:- Beltrami/Lamb-vector fragility is also already on record.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:69:- Once Step 3 uses Beltrami perturbations, the chain overlaps materially with Chain 03.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:77:- Step 3's kill condition is actually reasonable if the target is a generic NS mechanism, but then it makes the branch nearly predetermined because prior context already says Beltrami cancellation is highly fragile.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:100:If this chain is kept, it should be treated as a short obstruction-hunting branch, not a full four-step attack path. The honest version is: front-load the Tao filter, demand an estimate-level improvement by the end of Step 2, and stop immediately if the only surviving signal is Beltrami-alignment fragility, because that is geometry-branch material rather than an SQG-type algebraic breakthrough.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:1:# Chain 04 - Adapted-Package Geometric Vorticity Route From Local Beltrami Deficit To Criterion Scale
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:5:The old neutral-Eulerian geometry package is already weak, so geometry is live only if the package change is stated openly and audited honestly. This chain asks whether one adapted localization package can turn local Beltrami deficit, direction coherence, or tube persistence into a theorem-facing geometric criterion or full-stretching reduction without hiding the gain inside the package itself.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:25:- Action: choose one promoted observable family only: local Beltrami deficit, direction coherence, Beltrami-plus-concentration, or direction-coherence-plus-persistence.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:63:Action: test the definitions on edge cases already visible in the inherited context: exact Beltrami cancellation, mirror-mode completion, nearly degenerate triads, and packets with tiny but dynamically decisive trigger modes.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:1:# Attack on Chain 03 - Geometric Vorticity Alignment and Local Beltrami Tubes
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:- local Beltrami alignment (`u` nearly parallel to `omega`)
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The chosen observables do not naturally feed one another. Small local Beltrami deficit controls `u x omega`, but Constantin-Fefferman type criteria care about spatial regularity of the vorticity direction field. A flow can be pointwise near-Beltrami inside each tube core while `xi` varies wildly from tube to tube or even across nearby filaments.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:22:- The kill condition is too soft. The chain should die not only if known geometric criteria are "too nonlocal," but also if every bridge from local Beltrami deficit to those criteria passes through derivative control of `xi` or some comparably stronger hypothesis. That is not a technical nuisance. That is the obstruction.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:26:### Step 2 - Quantify depletion from local Beltrami structure
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The anchor case is pointed at the wrong object. Exact Beltrami structure annihilates the Lamb vector `u x omega`, but the dangerous term in the vorticity equation is vortex stretching, i.e. `(omega · grad)u = S omega`. Small `u x omega` does not by itself imply small `S omega` or small `S omega · omega`.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The step quietly assumes a perturbative principle that the mission context already warns against. Exact Beltrami cancellation is known to be extremely fragile. Localizing the condition to high-vorticity regions does not cure that fragility, because the strain and pressure are nonlocal.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:33:- "Using exact-Beltrami cancellation as the anchor case" risks importing De Giorgi/pressure intuition into a vorticity-stretching problem. The two phenomena are related only indirectly. This step needs a direct path from local alignment to control of `S omega`, not a memory of a different cancellation.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:47:This step should be judged by a much stricter standard: does it create a genuinely new implication from local Beltrami geometry to a known regularity mechanism? If not, it should terminate as a negative result, not be upgraded into a "draft proposition."
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:60:- The chain conflates Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence. They are related heuristically, not quantitatively. Treating them as one mechanism is the central structural flaw.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- The success criterion is too forgiving. "Conditional statement or conjecture" is cheap. The chain should count as success only if it proves a new scale-appropriate bridge from local Beltrami deficit to an existing regularity criterion, or else a rigorous obstruction showing why no such bridge exists.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- There is partial prior-art redundancy. Without a hard Beltrami-to-criterion bridge, the chain collapses back into known Constantin-Fefferman style regularity conditions plus suggestive tube language.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:- The bridge from local Beltrami structure to known geometric criteria is the whole problem, not a downstream detail.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:83:Treat it as a short obstruction hunt, not a long proof path. The first question should be whether any scale-critical estimate links local Beltrami deficit on high-`|omega|` sets to control of `S omega` or to a known vorticity-direction criterion. If the answer is no, the right output is a sharp fragility memo: local near-Beltrami geometry is a descriptive feature of vortex tubes, not an operational regularity lever.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:34:- Restricting to one promoted mechanism is good discipline, but it happens too late. The prior-art benchmark should come before promotion, not after. Otherwise the chain can spend time promoting a mechanism that is just a repackaging of Waleffe-type helical interaction lore, Beltrami depletion rhetoric, or decimated-shell intuition.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:67:- The route is highly exposed to prior-art overlap. Helical-sign classes, Beltrami depletion, restricted interaction geometry, and shell-transfer rhetoric have been mined for years. The chain recognizes this, but too late. The literature filter should be front-loaded, not attached after mechanism promotion.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The likely honest output is therefore a sharp negative memo: the coupled invariant structure is exact but too non-coercive, too prior-art-adjacent, or too fragile under mixed-helicity restoration and localization to move a real continuation or blowup bottleneck.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- Banning pure energy reformulations and pure same-helicity folklore is necessary, but it does not solve the deeper problem that helicity may still enter only decoratively. A chain can avoid literal energy-only language while still deriving nothing stronger than energy control plus polarized bookkeeping.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:51:- Mixed-helicity interactions are not a perturbation of the good regime. They are the default full-equation environment. If the gain depends on coherent helicity sign or favorable polarization, then mixed-helicity restoration is not one late test among many. It is the central obstacle and should have been front-loaded.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- The negative menu is sensible but too clean. The route may fail for several reasons at once: no one-sided quantity, prior-art collapse, mixed-helicity restoration, and localization failure. Forcing a single typed obstruction can underreport how overdetermined the failure really is.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:86:Most of the chain's genuine discipline is negative: do not confuse decompositions, do not stop at same-helicity folklore, do not ignore restoration debt. That makes it a credible obstruction program. It does not make it a credible proof route.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:98:- The chain is right to insist that pure energy-flux rewrites and same-helicity folklore are not enough.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:99:- Step 4 at least names the real debts: mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, viscosity, and localization.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:107:So the chain is worth running only if it is understood as a short route to a calibrated no-go. If it tries to become a proof program before exhibiting a precise coercive quantity that survives mixed-helicity restoration and localization, it will mostly manufacture elegant invariant rhetoric around a structurally weak idea.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/selected/chain-01.md:41:- Action: test whether an apparent gain is really pressure-localization nostalgia, near-Beltrami geometry, or another effect better treated in a different branch.
