missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:24:### Chain 03 - Geometric Vorticity Alignment and Local Beltrami Tubes
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:26:Central premise: Tao averaging keeps harmonic analysis but destroys fine vortex geometry. Exact Beltrami annihilates the Lamb vector, so the natural question is whether local near-Beltrami structure on intense-vorticity regions can be linked to Constantin-Fefferman style control.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:28:Central premise: the real NS nonlinearity moves both energy and helicity, and the joint transfer geometry may be stronger than the energy-only or triad-only pictures already audited. A live mechanism would have to survive full mixed-helicity restoration and yield a theorem-relevant depletion or no-bad-cascade statement.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/winning-chain.md:93:- Action: do not count near-Beltrami or special alignment as success by itself, but also do not discard a hybrid mechanism just because it is not purely algebraic.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:20:This branch is still about whether the exact NS algebra can be operationalized into a better nonlinear mechanism, but it is no longer a general search over pretty identities. It is an estimate-first screen tied directly to the mission bottleneck and separated from geometry-first Beltrami analysis.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:55:- Action: if one candidate appears to improve the estimate, test whether the gain is genuinely algebraic and generic or merely a near-Beltrami / alignment effect.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:56:- Action: use Beltrami only as a fragility screen, not as positive evidence. Specify the perturbation metric before testing.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:60:- Kill condition: if the candidate only survives in exact or near-exact Beltrami-style alignment, record "geometry branch only" and close this chain as an algebraic dead end.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:45:The mission context already records that the vorticity formulation also hits the same `beta = 4/3` barrier, and that Beltrami cancellation is extremely fragile. That does not make this chain pointless, but it does mean parts of Step 2 and Step 3 are at risk of spending budget re-certifying known negatives rather than testing genuinely live candidates.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:81:- The chain waits until after a candidate "appears to improve the estimate" before asking whether the effect is just alignment. That is backwards for this mission. Given what is already known about Beltrami fragility, geometry should be built into the first evaluation, not added as a later purity test.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:84:- The step uses near-Beltrami mainly as a fragility screen. That is fair as a guardrail, but it ignores the possibility that localized high-vorticity regions are exactly where one should expect any non-averaged NS structure to manifest.
