# Meta Note - Step 001 Exploration 001

## What Worked

- Separating the raw triad-phase ledger from later scalar summaries prevented
  the branch from promoting an aggregation convention as if it were an
  intrinsic object.
- Using coefficient-corrected interaction phases made the admissibility test
  line up with exact transfer structure rather than with packet labels.

## Reusable Lesson

- When a mission asks for an intrinsic phase/coherence object, promote the
  orbit-level exact interaction data first and demote scalar coherence scores
  to diagnostics unless the aggregation law itself is symmetry-forced.

## Caution

- A desired-vs-spectator phase score can look mathematically tidy while still
  being definitionally inadmissible if the raw formula names the target route
  by hand.

