+# Exploration 001 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Classify the canonical first-budget seed families for one exact triad orbit on
+the frozen canonical helical support sheet.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Read the Step-2 goal, the full Step-1 freeze, and the controller decision
+  that opened this budget.
+- Reused the Step-1 equivalence sheet to decide what can and cannot be
+  quotiented away at the seed-definition stage.
+- Screened out repeated-wavevector and collinear "triads" using the Step-1
+  exact interaction scalar before cataloging the honest seeds.
+
+## Outcome
+
+`succeeded`
+
+## One Key Takeaway
+
+The honest first-budget catalog is small:
+every seed is a nondegenerate noncollinear one-triad helical seed
+`k = p + q`
+modulo conjugation, `p <-> q`, and global helical-sign relabeling, and the raw
+helical sign triples reduce to three canonical classes:
+`(+++)`, `(++-)`, and `(+--)`.
+Repeated-wavevector or collinear cases are excluded because they are not exact
+active triads with nonzero projected coefficient.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Run the closure audit uniformly across those three sign-sheet classes; the
+  real question is no longer seed definition but whether conjugate-completed
+  off-orbit pairs force new modes immediately.
+- Keep the catalog coarse unless a later budget genuinely needs a finer
+  geometry split.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- The local record is sharp enough to exclude degenerate "triads" already at
+  the seed-definition stage, so they should not be listed as dead survivors
+  later.
+- The sign-sheet quotient is finite enough for Step 2, but not so strong that
+  mixed sign classes can be collapsed into one seed without argument.
