+# Meta Note - Step 002 Exploration 002
+
+## What Worked
+
+- The exact closure obstruction was already visible on the first honest pass:
+  mirror completion created off-orbit pairs that forced new wavevectors before
+  any detailed reduced dynamics or long recursive tower was needed.
+- Using the Step-1 ambient interaction scalar kept the argument at exact
+  Navier-Stokes support level instead of drifting into schematic support-graph
+  rhetoric.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- In exact-support audits, mirror-cross pairs created by mandatory conjugate
+  completion are often the decisive first spill mechanism; checking only the
+  visually intended orbit almost always understates the true closure burden.
+
+## Caution
+
+- Self-pairs are an easy distraction.
+  A tidy support can fail because of distinct off-orbit pairs even when
+  same-wavevector doubling vanishes identically.
