+
+## What Worked
+
+- Treating the mirror-complete one-triad picture as a pseudo-survivor worth an
+  admissible-enlargement audit sharpened the negative without pretending a real
+  survivor existed.
+- The shared-mode enlargement on `p - q` showed that the step's own
+  enlargement policy agrees with the closure negative rather than weakening it.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- When a budget produces no honest survivor, the enlargement pass can still be
+  valuable if it is used to prove that the most tempting tidy picture is only
+  an over-pruned artifact of stopping closure too early.
+
+## Caution
+
+- A clean current-budget negative does not authorize a mission-level failure
+  claim and does not self-authorize escalation to the next budget.
